result.execSummary:
The defendant Nykeem R Abdullah was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Theft-Movable Property <=$2500 [Modifiers: Party to a Crime], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.20(1)(a).
  • Entry into/onto Bldg/Constuct.Site/Room [Modifiers: Party to a Crime], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.15(1).
  • Resisting or Obstructing an Officer, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.41(1).

Defendant Nykeem R Abdullah in court with attorney Odalo Joseph Ohiku.  Defendant Nykeem R Abdullah in custody.  Michael Lonski   Defendant was advised of constitutional rights and maximum penalties, waived all rights, plead GUILTY and was examined as to the plea.  Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights and Addendum received and filed.  Parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis for the plea.  Defendant further advised that if he is not a US citizen deportation is possible.  Court found defendant guilty as charged in the Information and ordered entry of Judgment of Conviction.
Sentencing proceeded.  Statements made by State, Defense and Defendant.

AS TO COUNT 1:
The Court sentenced defendant to serve 6 MONTHS in the House of Corrections, consecutive to COUNT 2 and 3, straight time for the first 4 months of sentence, remaining balance with Huber release privileges for work or Day Reporting Center.  Court STAYED sentence and placed the defendant on PROBATION for a period of 2 YEARS with the following conditions:
-Parties stipulate to the amount of $100.00, join/several with any other co-actors who may be charged with this offense.  Remaining balance to be paid upon conclusion of the restitution hearing.  Court ordered restitution be paid prior to any court costs, surcharges and assessments are paid.  
-Court costs and victim/witness surcharges are to be collected during term of probation; nonpayment penalty shall be a civil judgment
-Defendant to pay the DNA surcharge during term of probation; nonpayment penalty shall result in a civil judgment
-No new law violations rising to the level of probable cause
-No association with drug users, drug dealers and drug houses or otherwise engate in drug dealing
-Cooperate with agent
-Obtain/maintain employment unless in school.  If in school full-time, defendant to have a part-time job 
-Obtain GED or HSED
-Successfully complete a Cognitive Thinking Behavioral Modification Program
-No contact with Marlon J, Emile R. and 929 E. Clarke Street 
-AODA assessment and any recommended treatment
-Absolute sobriety with random urine screens and breathalyzers
-No alcohol or controlled substances

AS TO COUNT 2:
Court sentenced the defendant to 6 MONTHS in the House of Corrections, straight time, consecutive to COUNT 1 and 3, with credit for 93 days time served.  No electronic monitoring. 
-Court costs and victim/witness surcharges are to be collected during term of probation on COUNTS 1 and 3; nonpayment penalty shall result in a civil judgment
-Defendant to pay the DNA surcharge during term of probaiton; nonpayment penalty shall result in a civil judgment

AS TO COUNT 3:
The Court sentenced defendant to serve 6 MONTHS in the House of Corrections, consecutive to COUNT 1 and 2, straight time for the first 4 months of sentence, remaining balance with Huber release privileges for work or Day Reporting Center.  Court STAYED sentence and placed the defendant on PROBATION for a period of 2 YEARS with the following conditions:
